Defense Threat Reduction Agency (DTRA) - SQL Database Development Initiative -- $1.8M Budget
Question: How did you allocate the budget across different divisions in the SQL Database Development Initiative?

•	Allocated $600,000 to Database Design and Development.

•	Allocated $500,000 to IT Infrastructure for necessary upgrades.

•	Allocated $400,000 to Data Compliance and Security for audits and policy development.

•	Allocated $300,000 to Training for developing and delivering database training programs.

•	Ensured resources were available to achieve divisional objectives while maintaining overall program cohesion.
